        "text_pdwXRr": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We are here to make goods that we are proud of, both for their function and their beauty. A commitment to a fair and caring work environment is at the core of our philosophy. The price points of our handmade ceramics are dictated by carefully calculating the time and energy that go into each piece, and supporting a fair and decent wage for all of our team members. We source our clay from a local manufacturer before hand making, trimming, glazing and firing all of our pieces at our studio in Hood River. Many of our forms are hand-thrown on a potter’s wheel, and in recent years we’ve also begun embracing other pottery tools that allow us to grow and be kinder to our bodies.</p>"
          }
        }
