            "hover-image": "shopify://shop_images/WolfCeramics_June2023-81.jpg",
            "title": "Glazing Mugs",
            "text": "<p>Glaze consists of clay and mineral particles suspended in water. Bisqueware must be dipped consistently and in one swift motion to avoid drips and blemishes. After glazing, the ceramics are carefully touched up with a sponge and an Exacto knife before being loaded into the kiln for a second firing!</p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        },
        "column_deXNkR": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/IMG_6501.jpg",
            "hover-image": "shopify://shop_images/IMG_6509.jpg",
            "title": "Glazing Dinnerware",
            "text": "<p>Most of our dinnerware forms are dipped twice, once on each side, leaving a stripe of glaze overlap at the center of the piece. This double dip technique is a mark of our process and of the fact that we glaze our wares by hand, rather than using a spray booth. We love this mark and consider it an aesthetic signature of our line!</p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        },
        "column_jG36kT": {
